  "signature": "ed25519:038088b4a164eeacc15dfb5c3ba10ab6b78a90cca3f6c00fd3a187db993ff291dc3c568c9333411925747d52618d14f0961694b62f11b00ea27483ceaf08c903",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl5-class3",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2024R1) is operated under a documented software quality assurance plan compliant with FDA guidance on software validation. Version control, regression testing suite (>800 test cases), and configuration management records are archived. SQA audit completed by independent reviewer; no open findings. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4 for MRL 5 Class III device context."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed using the method of manufactured solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations and the power-law hemolysis transport equation. Observed order of accuracy (1.97) is consistent with the theoretical second-order spatial accuracy of the discretization scheme. Results documented in code verification report CVR-2024-07. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted on three mesh levels (6M, 18M, 54M elements) using Richardson extrapolation. Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index at the design operating point is 2.3%, well within the 5% acceptance threshold for MRL 5. Temporal convergence verified with three time-step sizes; discretization error budget documented in report DER-2024-09. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, temperature) are documented with calibrated instrumentation traceable to NIST standards. Uncertainty in boundary conditions is quantified and propagated through the Monte Carlo UQ campaign. All 5 operating points replicated in both bench and CFD environments with documented parameter matching. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of CFD-predicted hemolysis index against bench measurements performed using normalized index of agreement (NIA) and E_rms metrics. NIA = 0.94 across all 5 operating points (threshold: ≥0.90). Velocity field comparison with PIV data yields mean relative error of 4.1% in the blade passage region. Comparison documented in validation report VR-2024-11 with full uncertainty bounds. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI — normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) — is the clinically accepted metric for blood damage assessment in VAD devices and directly maps to the regulatory decision threshold. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress distribution, exposure time histograms) are documented as supporting evidence. Clinical relevance of NIH to patient hemolysis outcomes is supported by peer-reviewed literature and FDA guidance. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device — using blood-analog fluid (40% glycerin-water) at physiologically representative operating conditions. Geometric similarity is exact; fluid dynamic similarity (Reynolds number, flow coefficient) is within 3% of clinical operating range. Relevance assessment documented in relevance matrix RM-2024-06. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence verified by monitoring residuals to below 1e-6 for all equations and confirming global mass and momentum imbalances below 0.01%. Round-off error assessed through double-precision arithmetic verification. Solver error contribution to total hemolysis index uncertainty estimated at <0.5% via sensitivity analysis. Documented in solver error report SER-2024-08. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second qualified engineer independent of the analyst. Boundary condition assignments, turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), hemolysis model parameters, and post-processing scripts were independently verified against documented simulation plan SP-2024-05. No discrepancies identified. Use error controls documented in quality record QR-2024-10. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation) is assessed for applicability to the shear stress and exposure time ranges present in the centrifugal pump. Model form uncertainty is quantified by comparing predictions from three alternative hemolysis models (Taskin, Zhang, and modified Giersiepen) across all operating points; spread in NIH predictions is 8.2% and is incorporated into the total uncertainty budget. Model form assessment documented in MFA-2024-12. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (fluid density, viscosity, hemolysis model coefficients, pump geometry dimensions, rotational speed) are characterized with probability distributions derived from measurement data or literature. Monte Carlo sampling (10,000 samples) propagates input uncertainty to hemolysis index predictions. 95th percentile NIH prediction remains below clinical threshold. Input uncertainty documentation in report IUR-2024-10. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Bench hemolysis measurements performed on n=6 replicate pump assemblies across all 5 operating points (30 total test runs). Sample-to-sample variability in NIH is 6.4% (1σ), consistent with published inter-laboratory variability data. Test sample documentation includes pump serial numbers, fluid batch records, and measurement uncertainty analysis per ASTM F1841. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Equivalency between CFD model input parameters and experimental test parameters is established through a parameter mapping matrix covering all 12 primary inputs. Dimensional analysis confirms Reynolds number similarity within 2.1% between bench and CFD conditions. Discrepancies in fluid temperature (±1.5°C) and viscosity (±3%) are within the uncertainty budget and their effect on NIH is quantified as <1.8% via sensitivity analysis. Equivalency assessment documented in EQV-2024-11. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-nc2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and all achieved levels meet or exceed the required levels for Model Risk Level 5 (Class III VAD device). Key evidence supporting acceptance: (1) Code verification via MMS confirms second-order spatial accuracy; (2) Mesh refinement study yields GCI <2.5% for the hemolysis QoI; (3) Quantitative validation against PIV and bench hemolysis data achieves NIA=0.94, exceeding the 0.90 threshold; (4) Monte Carlo UQ with 10,000 samples demonstrates that the 95th percentile NIH prediction remains below the clinical acceptance threshold with margin; (5) Model form uncertainty from three alternative hemolysis models is bounded at 8.2% and incorporated in the total uncertainty budget; (6) All validation activities were conducted on the same FDA generic pump geometry under physiologically representative conditions, establishing high relevance to the COU. The structured evidence chain from foundational experimental data through uncertainty quantification to the regulatory decision is complete and traceable. No credibility gaps remain unaddressed. The computational model is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the hemolysis regulatory submission for this Class III VAD device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
